    • Method Detail

      • isApplicable

        public boolean isApplicable(BasicObligation obl)
        Description copied from interface: Processor
        this is a short test whether this processor can in general handle this kind of basic obligation. This information will be used for two things. First, if the processor says that it is not applicable, it will not be tried with process. (Hence, all input passed to process will be checked with isApplicable) Second, in an interactive mode, this method can be used to determine which processors may be applied to the currently selected obligation.
        Specified by:
        isApplicable in interface Processor
        Overrides:
        isApplicable in class IntTRSNontermProcessor

      • process

        public Result process(BasicObligation obl,
                      BasicObligationNode oblNode,
                      Abortion aborter,
                      RuntimeInformation rti)
               throws AbortionException
        Description copied from interface: Processor
        Computes the result of this processor applied on obl.
        Parameters:
        obl - - the basic obligation that should be processed
        oblNode - - the position of the basic obligation in the obligation tree
        aborter - - the aborter, that should be checked many times against timeouts/aborts, ...
        rti - - the runtime information should only be used to build new executable strategies for the result. This information can be ignored for all processors that deliver only Success or Fail as resulting strategies.
        Returns:
        the result of this processor
        Throws:
        AbortionException
